overbought and trade above my intrinsic value -- it happens all the time. And I wouldn't be surprised if it happened in the next few weeks. Over the next few months the downside appears to be limited by the scope and size of the Fed's bazooka and the upside is likely limited by

the magnitude of the necessary financial relief packages and the massive rise in the U.S. debt load that will, in the fullness of time, adversely impact economic growth. As I have written in recent years in my Diary, it takes more and more stimulus (and associated debt that

accompanies that jump start) to deliver a unit of production. Intermediate term and on a normalization of business activity we can go higher because there is no alternative with short-term notes effectively at zero. A "TINA RIPPER" is not out of the question some time later
